<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="85" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/4779</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-18">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2664. Your 2459, September 5. Communicate with Foreign Office and
                                state that in view of removal of firms in United States from black
                                list Department is at loss to understand attitude of French
                                authorities. Letters of Carl Grubnau giving further details going
                                forward by mail.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>